}\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Andy Granda]]|CUB}}\n|-\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Inal Tasoev]]|RUS}}\n|}\n\n===Women's events===\n{| {{MedalistTable|type=Event|labelwidth=180}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Extra-lightweight (-48&nbsp;kg)\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Daria Bilodid]]|UKR}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Wakana Koga]]|JPN}}\n|{{flagmedalist|[[M\u00e9lanie Clement]]|FRA}}\n|-\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Urantsetseg Munkhbat]]|MGL}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Half-lightweight (-52&nbsp;kg)\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Distria Krasniqi]]|KOS}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Odette Giuffrida]]|ITA}}\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Ai Shishime]]|JPN}}\n|-\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Larissa Pimenta]]|BRA}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Lightweight (-57&nbsp;kg)\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Christa Deguchi]]|CAN}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Sumiya Dorjsuren]]|MGL}}\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Momo Tamaoki]]|JPN}}\n|-\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Nora Gjakova]]|KOS}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Half-middleweight (-63&nbsp;kg)\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Clarisse Agbegnenou]]|FRA}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Nami Nabekura]]|JPN}}\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Tina Trstenjak]]|SLO}}\n|-\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Masako Doi]]|JPN}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Middleweight (-70&nbsp;kg)\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Yoko Ono (judoka)|Yoko Ono]]|JPN}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Saki Niizoe]]|JPN}}\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Gemma Howell]]|GBR}}\n|-\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Anna Bernholm]]|SWE}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Half-heavyweight (-78&nbsp;kg)\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Madeleine Malonga]]|FRA}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Fanny Posvite]]|FRA}}\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Mami Umeki]]|JPN}}\n|-\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Kaliema Antomarchi]]|CUB}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|Heavyweight (+78&nbsp;kg)\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Romane Dicko]]|FRA}}\n|rowspan=2|{{flagmedalist|[[Maryna Slutskaya]]|BLR}}\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Beatriz Souza]]|BRA}}\n|-\n|{{flagmedalist|[[Rochele Nunes]]|POR}}\n|}\n\nIn Paris, the Chinese delegation could not participate because of visa issues due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>[https://www.ijf.org/news/show/riner-set-to-return-as-accorhotels-arena-nears-sell-out Riner set to return as AccorHotels Arena nears sell-out]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.ijf.org/competition/2017 Competition page], International Judo Federation\n*[https://www.judoinside.com/event/15001/2020_Grand_Slam_Paris/judo-results The Competition] at JudoInside.com\n\n[[Category:2020 IJF World Tour]]\n[[Category:2020 Judo Grand Slam|Paris]]\n[[Category:Sports competitions in Paris]]\n[[Category:2020 in French sport|Judo]]\n[[Category:February 2020 sports events in France|Judo]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Judo competition}}\n{{Infobox sports competition event\n|competition    = 2020 Judo Grand Slam Paris\n|image          = \n|dates          = 8\u20139 February 2020\n|competitors    = 688\n|nations        = 117\n|venue          = [[AccorHotels Arena]], [[Paris]]\n|location       = [[Paris]], [[France]]\n|prev           = [[2020 Judo Grand Prix Tel Aviv|2020 Tel Aviv]]\n|next           = [[2020 Judo Grand Slam D\u00fcsseldorf|2020 D\u00fcsseldorf]]\n}}\n\nThe 2020 Judo [[Grand Slam Paris]] was held in [[Paris]], [[France]], from 8 - 9 February.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ijf.org/competition/2017|title=Paris Grand Slam 2020, International Judo Federation website|work=www.ijf.org|accessdate=8 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Medal summary==\n===Medal table===\n<!--do not remove the \"*\", per WP:ACCESS-->\n{{Color box|#ccccff|&nbsp;<nowiki>*</nowiki>&nbsp;|border=darkgray}} Host nation\n{{Medals table\n | caption        = \n | host           = \n | flag_template  = \n | event          = \n | team           = \n | gold_JPN = 3 | silver_JPN = 5 | bronze_JPN = 5\n | gold_FRA = 3 | silver_FRA = 1 | bronze_FRA = 2 | host_FRA = yes\n | gold_KOR = 1 | silver_KOR = 1 | bronze_KOR = 0\n | gold_CAN = 1 | silver_CAN = 0 | bronze_CAN = 1\n | gold_UKR = 1 | silver_UKR = 0 | bronze_UKR = 1\n | gold_NED = 1 | silver_NED = 0 | bronze_NED = 1\n | gold_KOS = 1 | silver_